The course indoctrinates the historiosophical ideas of famous Russian thinkers (Chaadaev, Herzen, the Slavophils, V. Solovyov, Berdiaev, Frank, Fedotov, et al.), acquaints with the phenomenon of Russian intelligenzia as a characteristics of Russian culture and introduces the modern sociological and historical theories in the field of nationalism. The idea of national identity and its development in Russian culture is studied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to develop critical thinking, the ability to compare various points of view and to formulate one's own position.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student: 1)	has the idea about the process of formation of the ideas of nation and nationalism on the basis of Russian culture; 2)	is aware with the historiosophical ideas of famous Russian thinkers (Chaadaev, Herzen, the Slavophils, V. Solovyov, Berdiaev, Frank, Fedotov, et al.);  3)	knows the modern sociological and historical theories in the field of nationalism; 4)	understands the phenomenon of Russian intelligenzia as a characteristics of Russian culture; 5)	can meet the challenges of contemporary world in the field of nationalism; 6) can take a stand and express his\her opinion on the presentations of the other students.
